INSERT INTO public.questions (id, question_type, difficulty, topic, question, answer, quiz, match_keywords, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (62, 'single_choice', 'hard', 'Architectural pattern', '<p>What&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;connection&nbsp;between&nbsp;DDD&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;pattern?</p>', '<p>In&nbsp;DDD-based&nbsp;systems&nbsp;with&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;bounded&nbsp;contexts,&nbsp;the&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;pattern&nbsp;coordinates&nbsp;long-running&nbsp;or&nbsp;distributed&nbsp;business&nbsp;transactions&nbsp;by&nbsp;orchestrating&nbsp;domain&nbsp;events&nbsp;or&nbsp;commands&nbsp;across&nbsp;services,&nbsp;ensuring&nbsp;eventual&nbsp;consistency&nbsp;where&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;ACID&nbsp;transaction&nbsp;is&nbsp;not&nbsp;possible.</p><p></p><p>Wrong&nbsp;answers:</p><ul><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;pattern&nbsp;replaces&nbsp;aggregates&nbsp;in&nbsp;DDD&nbsp;entirely,&nbsp;allowing&nbsp;domain&nbsp;models&nbsp;to&nbsp;be&nbsp;discarded&nbsp;in&nbsp;favor&nbsp;of&nbsp;centralized&nbsp;transaction&nbsp;controllers.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;do&nbsp;not&nbsp;replace&nbsp;aggregates;&nbsp;they&nbsp;coordinate&nbsp;processes&nbsp;between&nbsp;aggregates&nbsp;or&nbsp;bounded&nbsp;contexts.</li></ul></li><li>DDD&nbsp;requires&nbsp;every&nbsp;bounded&nbsp;context&nbsp;to&nbsp;include&nbsp;exactly&nbsp;one&nbsp;Saga,&nbsp;making&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;the&nbsp;mandatory&nbsp;entry&nbsp;point&nbsp;for&nbsp;all&nbsp;commands&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;domain&nbsp;layer.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;DDD&nbsp;does&nbsp;not&nbsp;mandate&nbsp;Sagas;&nbsp;they&nbsp;are&nbsp;optional&nbsp;and&nbsp;used&nbsp;only&nbsp;for&nbsp;cross-context,&nbsp;long-running&nbsp;workflows.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;pattern&nbsp;eliminates&nbsp;the&nbsp;need&nbsp;for&nbsp;domain&nbsp;events&nbsp;in&nbsp;DDD&nbsp;because&nbsp;it&nbsp;forces&nbsp;all&nbsp;services&nbsp;to&nbsp;share&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;transactional&nbsp;database.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;commonly&nbsp;use&nbsp;domain&nbsp;events,&nbsp;and&nbsp;they&nbsp;explicitly&nbsp;support&nbsp;distributed&nbsp;systems—not&nbsp;shared&nbsp;databases.</li></ul></li><li>In&nbsp;DDD,&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;act&nbsp;as&nbsp;repositories&nbsp;that&nbsp;store&nbsp;the&nbsp;full&nbsp;history&nbsp;of&nbsp;an&nbsp;aggregate’s&nbsp;state,&nbsp;allowing&nbsp;developers&nbsp;to&nbsp;rebuild&nbsp;domain&nbsp;objects&nbsp;without&nbsp;event&nbsp;sourcing.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;are&nbsp;process&nbsp;managers,&nbsp;not&nbsp;state&nbsp;stores;&nbsp;they&nbsp;do&nbsp;not&nbsp;function&nbsp;as&nbsp;repositories&nbsp;or&nbsp;event&nbsp;stores.</li></ul></li><li>Sagas&nbsp;are&nbsp;used&nbsp;in&nbsp;DDD&nbsp;to&nbsp;merge&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;bounded&nbsp;contexts&nbsp;into&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;context,&nbsp;removing&nbsp;boundaries&nbsp;so&nbsp;transactions&nbsp;become&nbsp;simpler&nbsp;and&nbsp;fully&nbsp;synchronous.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;preserve&nbsp;boundaries&nbsp;and&nbsp;handle&nbsp;coordination;&nbsp;they&nbsp;do&nbsp;not&nbsp;merge&nbsp;bounded&nbsp;contexts.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;pattern&nbsp;in&nbsp;DDD&nbsp;forces&nbsp;aggregates&nbsp;to&nbsp;expose&nbsp;their&nbsp;internal&nbsp;state&nbsp;directly&nbsp;so&nbsp;compensating&nbsp;actions&nbsp;can&nbsp;update&nbsp;them&nbsp;without&nbsp;going&nbsp;through&nbsp;domain&nbsp;rules.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Aggregates&nbsp;never&nbsp;expose&nbsp;internal&nbsp;state&nbsp;directly;&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;interact&nbsp;via&nbsp;commands&nbsp;or&nbsp;events,&nbsp;respecting&nbsp;domain&nbsp;invariants.</li></ul></li><li>DDD&nbsp;prohibits&nbsp;the&nbsp;use&nbsp;of&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;because&nbsp;they&nbsp;introduce&nbsp;eventual&nbsp;consistency,&nbsp;which&nbsp;is&nbsp;incompatible&nbsp;with&nbsp;the&nbsp;strict&nbsp;transactional&nbsp;guarantees&nbsp;required&nbsp;in&nbsp;all&nbsp;bounded&nbsp;contexts.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;DDD&nbsp;explicitly&nbsp;supports&nbsp;eventual&nbsp;consistency&nbsp;across&nbsp;contexts,&nbsp;and&nbsp;Sagas&nbsp;are&nbsp;a&nbsp;common&nbsp;pattern&nbsp;for&nbsp;handling&nbsp;exactly&nbsp;that.</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, '{}', true, '2025-12-05 11:47:16.179711+00', '2025-12-05 11:47:16.204531+00');
INSERT INTO public.questions (id, question_type, difficulty, topic, question, answer, quiz, match_keywords, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (14, 'multiple_choice', 'easy', 'Clean code', '<p>What&nbsp;are&nbsp;<strong>Immutable&nbsp;functions</strong>?</p>', '<p>A&nbsp;function&nbsp;that&nbsp;does&nbsp;not&nbsp;modify&nbsp;its&nbsp;input&nbsp;values&nbsp;and&nbsp;returns&nbsp;new&nbsp;data&nbsp;instead.</p><p></p><p>Correct&nbsp;answers:</p><ul><li>An&nbsp;immutable&nbsp;function&nbsp;does&nbsp;not&nbsp;modify&nbsp;the&nbsp;objects,&nbsp;arrays,&nbsp;or&nbsp;data&nbsp;structures&nbsp;passed&nbsp;into&nbsp;it.</li><li>Immutable&nbsp;functions&nbsp;return&nbsp;new&nbsp;values&nbsp;or&nbsp;new&nbsp;data&nbsp;structures&nbsp;instead&nbsp;of&nbsp;changing&nbsp;existing&nbsp;ones.</li><li>Immutable&nbsp;functions&nbsp;help&nbsp;avoid&nbsp;shared-state&nbsp;bugs&nbsp;because&nbsp;the&nbsp;original&nbsp;data&nbsp;remains&nbsp;unchanged.</li><li>Immutable&nbsp;functions&nbsp;often&nbsp;use&nbsp;shallow&nbsp;or&nbsp;deep&nbsp;copies&nbsp;to&nbsp;produce&nbsp;new&nbsp;versions&nbsp;of&nbsp;data.</li><li>Immutable&nbsp;functions&nbsp;naturally&nbsp;support&nbsp;safe&nbsp;undo,&nbsp;redo,&nbsp;and&nbsp;state&nbsp;history&nbsp;because&nbsp;previous&nbsp;versions&nbsp;remain&nbsp;intact.</li></ul><p></p><p>Wrong&nbsp;answers:</p><ul><li>A&nbsp;function&nbsp;is&nbsp;immutable&nbsp;as&nbsp;long&nbsp;as&nbsp;it&nbsp;does&nbsp;not&nbsp;modify&nbsp;global&nbsp;variables,&nbsp;even&nbsp;if&nbsp;it&nbsp;mutates&nbsp;the&nbsp;object&nbsp;given&nbsp;to&nbsp;it&nbsp;as&nbsp;an&nbsp;argument.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;mutating&nbsp;inputs&nbsp;breaks&nbsp;immutability.</li></ul></li><li>Immutable&nbsp;functions&nbsp;never&nbsp;allocate&nbsp;new&nbsp;memory&nbsp;since&nbsp;they&nbsp;reuse&nbsp;the&nbsp;same&nbsp;data&nbsp;structures&nbsp;to&nbsp;avoid&nbsp;duplication.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;they&nbsp;typically&nbsp;allocate&nbsp;new&nbsp;memory&nbsp;for&nbsp;new&nbsp;versions.</li></ul></li><li>An&nbsp;immutable&nbsp;function&nbsp;can&nbsp;freely&nbsp;mutate&nbsp;nested&nbsp;properties&nbsp;of&nbsp;an&nbsp;object&nbsp;as&nbsp;long&nbsp;as&nbsp;the&nbsp;top-level&nbsp;reference&nbsp;stays&nbsp;the&nbsp;same.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;immutability&nbsp;requires&nbsp;not&nbsp;mutating&nbsp;any&nbsp;part&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;data.</li></ul></li><li>A&nbsp;function&nbsp;that&nbsp;mutates&nbsp;an&nbsp;internal&nbsp;variable&nbsp;is&nbsp;still&nbsp;considered&nbsp;immutable&nbsp;as&nbsp;long&nbsp;as&nbsp;callers&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;see&nbsp;that&nbsp;mutation.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;hidden&nbsp;internal&nbsp;mutation&nbsp;still&nbsp;breaks&nbsp;immutability.</li></ul></li><li>Immutable&nbsp;functions&nbsp;require&nbsp;all&nbsp;inputs&nbsp;to&nbsp;be&nbsp;primitive&nbsp;values,&nbsp;since&nbsp;reference&nbsp;types&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;be&nbsp;handled&nbsp;immutably.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;immutable&nbsp;functions&nbsp;can&nbsp;work&nbsp;with&nbsp;all&nbsp;data&nbsp;types&nbsp;by&nbsp;cloning&nbsp;or&nbsp;copying.</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, '{}', true, '2025-12-03 11:53:57.210698+00', '2025-12-03 12:11:26.558941+00');
INSERT INTO public.questions (id, question_type, difficulty, topic, question, answer, quiz, match_keywords, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (32, 'text_input', 'medium', 'Frontend', '<p>How&nbsp;do&nbsp;you&nbsp;call&nbsp;the&nbsp;attack&nbsp;where&nbsp;an&nbsp;attacker&nbsp;injects&nbsp;malicious&nbsp;scripts&nbsp;into&nbsp;a&nbsp;website,&nbsp;causing&nbsp;other&nbsp;users’&nbsp;browsers&nbsp;to&nbsp;execute&nbsp;the&nbsp;attacker’s&nbsp;code?</p>', '<p><strong>XSS</strong>&nbsp;(Cross-Site&nbsp;Scripting)&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;vulnerability&nbsp;where&nbsp;an&nbsp;attacker&nbsp;injects&nbsp;malicious&nbsp;JavaScript&nbsp;into&nbsp;a&nbsp;web&nbsp;page&nbsp;viewed&nbsp;by&nbsp;other&nbsp;users.&nbsp;When&nbsp;executed&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;victim’s&nbsp;browser,&nbsp;the&nbsp;script&nbsp;can&nbsp;steal&nbsp;cookies,&nbsp;hijack&nbsp;sessions,&nbsp;modify&nbsp;page&nbsp;content,&nbsp;or&nbsp;perform&nbsp;actions&nbsp;as&nbsp;the&nbsp;user.&nbsp;XSS&nbsp;happens&nbsp;when&nbsp;user&nbsp;input&nbsp;is&nbsp;not&nbsp;properly&nbsp;sanitized&nbsp;or&nbsp;escaped.&nbsp;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;commonly&nbsp;exploited&nbsp;through&nbsp;forms,&nbsp;comments,&nbsp;URLs,&nbsp;or&nbsp;vulnerable&nbsp;templates.&nbsp;Defenses&nbsp;include&nbsp;output&nbsp;encoding,&nbsp;Content&nbsp;Security&nbsp;Policy,&nbsp;input&nbsp;validation,&nbsp;and&nbsp;avoiding&nbsp;unsafe&nbsp;HTML&nbsp;rendering.</p>', NULL, '{XSS}', true, '2025-12-03 14:05:31.576427+00', '2025-12-03 14:05:31.576427+00');
INSERT INTO public.questions (id, question_type, difficulty, topic, question, answer, quiz, match_keywords, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (25, 'single_choice', 'hard', 'Microservices', '<p>What&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Saga&nbsp;pattern</strong>?</p>', '<p>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;Pattern&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;way&nbsp;to&nbsp;manage&nbsp;long-running,&nbsp;multi-service&nbsp;transactions&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;distributed&nbsp;system&nbsp;without&nbsp;using&nbsp;a&nbsp;traditional&nbsp;ACID&nbsp;transaction.</p><p>Instead&nbsp;of&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;big&nbsp;transaction,&nbsp;a&nbsp;saga&nbsp;breaks&nbsp;the&nbsp;workflow&nbsp;into&nbsp;a&nbsp;sequence&nbsp;of&nbsp;smaller&nbsp;local&nbsp;transactions.</p><p>Each&nbsp;local&nbsp;transaction&nbsp;updates&nbsp;its&nbsp;own&nbsp;service/database&nbsp;and&nbsp;then&nbsp;triggers&nbsp;the&nbsp;next&nbsp;step.</p><p>If&nbsp;any&nbsp;step&nbsp;fails,&nbsp;the&nbsp;saga&nbsp;runs&nbsp;compensating&nbsp;actions&nbsp;to&nbsp;undo&nbsp;the&nbsp;already-completed&nbsp;steps.</p><p></p><p><strong>Wrong&nbsp;answers</strong>:</p><ul><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;Pattern&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;centralized&nbsp;workflow&nbsp;engine&nbsp;that&nbsp;locks&nbsp;all&nbsp;participating&nbsp;services&nbsp;until&nbsp;every&nbsp;operation&nbsp;finishes,&nbsp;ensuring&nbsp;full&nbsp;ACID&nbsp;guarantees&nbsp;across&nbsp;the&nbsp;system.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;sagas&nbsp;avoid&nbsp;central&nbsp;locking&nbsp;and&nbsp;do&nbsp;not&nbsp;provide&nbsp;ACID&nbsp;transactions.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;Pattern&nbsp;requires&nbsp;all&nbsp;microservices&nbsp;to&nbsp;share&nbsp;the&nbsp;same&nbsp;database&nbsp;schema&nbsp;so&nbsp;compensating&nbsp;actions&nbsp;can&nbsp;be&nbsp;applied&nbsp;directly&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;original&nbsp;tables.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;sagas&nbsp;exist&nbsp;because&nbsp;services&nbsp;do&nbsp;not&nbsp;share&nbsp;a&nbsp;database.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;Pattern&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;technique&nbsp;where&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;global&nbsp;transaction&nbsp;manager&nbsp;coordinates&nbsp;distributed&nbsp;commits&nbsp;using&nbsp;two-phase&nbsp;commit.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;two-phase&nbsp;commit&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;opposite&nbsp;of&nbsp;sagas.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;Pattern&nbsp;guarantees&nbsp;real-time&nbsp;consistency&nbsp;by&nbsp;forcing&nbsp;all&nbsp;steps&nbsp;to&nbsp;complete&nbsp;before&nbsp;any&nbsp;service&nbsp;can&nbsp;proceed&nbsp;with&nbsp;other&nbsp;requests.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;sagas&nbsp;provide&nbsp;eventual&nbsp;consistency,&nbsp;not&nbsp;real-time&nbsp;blocking.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;Pattern&nbsp;is&nbsp;used&nbsp;to&nbsp;automatically&nbsp;discover&nbsp;which&nbsp;service&nbsp;should&nbsp;run&nbsp;next&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;workflow&nbsp;by&nbsp;polling&nbsp;all&nbsp;services&nbsp;for&nbsp;their&nbsp;readiness.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;sagas&nbsp;follow&nbsp;a&nbsp;defined&nbsp;sequence&nbsp;or&nbsp;event&nbsp;choreography,&nbsp;not&nbsp;discovery&nbsp;polling.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;Pattern&nbsp;works&nbsp;only&nbsp;in&nbsp;synchronous&nbsp;request-response&nbsp;architectures&nbsp;because&nbsp;compensations&nbsp;must&nbsp;be&nbsp;triggered&nbsp;immediately.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;sagas&nbsp;typically&nbsp;rely&nbsp;on&nbsp;asynchronous&nbsp;messaging.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;Saga&nbsp;Pattern&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;refactoring&nbsp;technique&nbsp;that&nbsp;merges&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;microservices&nbsp;into&nbsp;one&nbsp;larger&nbsp;service&nbsp;to&nbsp;prevent&nbsp;distributed&nbsp;failure&nbsp;scenarios.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;sagas&nbsp;coordinate&nbsp;services,&nbsp;they&nbsp;do&nbsp;not&nbsp;merge&nbsp;them.</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, '{}', true, '2025-12-03 13:12:01.724103+00', '2025-12-03 13:12:01.73141+00');
