INSERT INTO public.questions (id, question_type, difficulty, topic, question, answer, quiz, match_keywords, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (72, 'multiple_choice', 'medium', 'NodeJS Event Loop', '<p>What&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;difference&nbsp;between&nbsp;<strong>microtasks&nbsp;vs&nbsp;macrotasks</strong>?</p>', '<p>Microtasks&nbsp;and&nbsp;macrotasks&nbsp;represent&nbsp;two&nbsp;scheduling&nbsp;queues&nbsp;in&nbsp;JavaScript&nbsp;runtimes.&nbsp;Microtasks&nbsp;(e.g.,&nbsp;promise&nbsp;callbacks)&nbsp;run&nbsp;immediately&nbsp;after&nbsp;the&nbsp;current&nbsp;execution&nbsp;stack&nbsp;completes,&nbsp;before&nbsp;the&nbsp;event&nbsp;loop&nbsp;advances&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;next&nbsp;macrotask.&nbsp;Macrotasks&nbsp;(e.g.,&nbsp;timers,&nbsp;I/O)&nbsp;execute&nbsp;one&nbsp;per&nbsp;loop&nbsp;iteration,&nbsp;after&nbsp;microtasks&nbsp;are&nbsp;fully&nbsp;drained.&nbsp;This&nbsp;ordering&nbsp;gives&nbsp;microtasks&nbsp;higher&nbsp;priority&nbsp;and&nbsp;ensures&nbsp;consistent&nbsp;resolution&nbsp;semantics&nbsp;across&nbsp;environments.</p><p></p><p><strong>Correct&nbsp;answers:</strong></p><ul><li>Microtasks&nbsp;are&nbsp;executed&nbsp;immediately&nbsp;after&nbsp;the&nbsp;current&nbsp;call&nbsp;stack&nbsp;clears&nbsp;and&nbsp;before&nbsp;the&nbsp;event&nbsp;loop&nbsp;proceeds&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;next&nbsp;macrotask.</li><li>Macrotasks&nbsp;represent&nbsp;operations&nbsp;such&nbsp;as&nbsp;timers&nbsp;and&nbsp;I/O&nbsp;events&nbsp;that&nbsp;execute&nbsp;one&nbsp;at&nbsp;a&nbsp;time&nbsp;in&nbsp;successive&nbsp;event-loop&nbsp;iterations.</li><li>Promise&nbsp;resolution&nbsp;handlers&nbsp;run&nbsp;as&nbsp;microtasks,&nbsp;giving&nbsp;them&nbsp;higher&nbsp;scheduling&nbsp;priority&nbsp;than&nbsp;timer&nbsp;callbacks.</li><li>A&nbsp;macrotask&nbsp;will&nbsp;not&nbsp;begin&nbsp;execution&nbsp;until&nbsp;the&nbsp;microtask&nbsp;queue&nbsp;has&nbsp;been&nbsp;fully&nbsp;drained&nbsp;for&nbsp;that&nbsp;iteration&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;event&nbsp;loop.</li><li>Microtask&nbsp;execution&nbsp;ordering&nbsp;is&nbsp;deterministic:&nbsp;all&nbsp;queued&nbsp;microtasks&nbsp;are&nbsp;processed&nbsp;before&nbsp;the&nbsp;next&nbsp;macrotask&nbsp;is&nbsp;started.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Wrong&nbsp;answers:</strong></p><ul><li>Microtasks&nbsp;execute&nbsp;only&nbsp;after&nbsp;all&nbsp;macrotasks&nbsp;and&nbsp;rendering&nbsp;steps&nbsp;have&nbsp;completed,&nbsp;giving&nbsp;them&nbsp;the&nbsp;lowest&nbsp;scheduling&nbsp;priority&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;event&nbsp;loop.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Microtasks&nbsp;run&nbsp;<strong>before</strong>&nbsp;the&nbsp;next&nbsp;macrotask,&nbsp;not&nbsp;after&nbsp;everything&nbsp;else.</li></ul></li><li>Macrotasks&nbsp;include&nbsp;operations&nbsp;such&nbsp;as&nbsp;promise&nbsp;callbacks&nbsp;and&nbsp;mutation&nbsp;observer&nbsp;notifications,&nbsp;which&nbsp;require&nbsp;immediate&nbsp;post-stack&nbsp;execution.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;callbacks&nbsp;and&nbsp;mutation&nbsp;observers&nbsp;are&nbsp;<strong>microtasks</strong>,&nbsp;not&nbsp;macrotasks.</li></ul></li><li>Microtasks&nbsp;are&nbsp;scheduled&nbsp;to&nbsp;run&nbsp;only&nbsp;during&nbsp;the&nbsp;poll&nbsp;phase&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;event&nbsp;loop&nbsp;and&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;execute&nbsp;in&nbsp;other&nbsp;phases.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Microtasks&nbsp;run&nbsp;<strong>after&nbsp;the&nbsp;current&nbsp;stack</strong>,&nbsp;independent&nbsp;of&nbsp;phases.</li></ul></li><li>Macrotasks&nbsp;must&nbsp;complete&nbsp;before&nbsp;any&nbsp;microtask&nbsp;can&nbsp;be&nbsp;scheduled,&nbsp;preventing&nbsp;microtasks&nbsp;from&nbsp;accumulating&nbsp;during&nbsp;synchronous&nbsp;execution.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Microtasks&nbsp;can&nbsp;be&nbsp;queued&nbsp;<strong>any&nbsp;time</strong>,&nbsp;including&nbsp;during&nbsp;synchronous&nbsp;code.</li></ul></li><li>A&nbsp;microtask&nbsp;may&nbsp;be&nbsp;postponed&nbsp;across&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;macrotask&nbsp;cycles&nbsp;if&nbsp;the&nbsp;runtime&nbsp;determines&nbsp;that&nbsp;postponement&nbsp;improves&nbsp;throughput.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;Microtasks&nbsp;run&nbsp;<strong>immediately</strong>&nbsp;before&nbsp;the&nbsp;next&nbsp;macrotask,&nbsp;not&nbsp;postponed&nbsp;arbitrarily.</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, '{}', true, '2025-12-05 12:38:16.725571+00', '2025-12-05 12:41:08.258121+00');
INSERT INTO public.questions (id, question_type, difficulty, topic, question, answer, quiz, match_keywords, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (6, 'multiple_choice', 'medium', 'JavaScript', '<p>What&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;JavaScript&nbsp;<strong>Promise</strong>?</p>', '<p>A&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;represents&nbsp;a&nbsp;value&nbsp;that&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;available&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;future.&nbsp;It&nbsp;handles&nbsp;asynchronous&nbsp;operations&nbsp;and&nbsp;lets&nbsp;you&nbsp;attach&nbsp;.then()&nbsp;for&nbsp;success&nbsp;and&nbsp;.catch()&nbsp;for&nbsp;errors.</p><p></p><p>Correct&nbsp;answers:</p><ul><li>.then()&nbsp;and&nbsp;.catch()&nbsp;callbacks&nbsp;always&nbsp;run&nbsp;asynchronously&nbsp;as&nbsp;microtasks,&nbsp;even&nbsp;if&nbsp;the&nbsp;promise&nbsp;is&nbsp;already&nbsp;resolved.</li><li>A&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;becomes&nbsp;permanently&nbsp;settled&nbsp;once&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;fulfilled&nbsp;or&nbsp;rejected&nbsp;and&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;change&nbsp;state&nbsp;afterward.</li><li>Throwing&nbsp;an&nbsp;error&nbsp;inside&nbsp;a&nbsp;.then()&nbsp;handler&nbsp;causes&nbsp;the&nbsp;next&nbsp;promise&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;chain&nbsp;to&nbsp;become&nbsp;rejected.</li><li>If&nbsp;you&nbsp;return&nbsp;another&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;inside&nbsp;.then(),&nbsp;the&nbsp;outer&nbsp;chain&nbsp;will&nbsp;wait&nbsp;for&nbsp;that&nbsp;inner&nbsp;promise&nbsp;to&nbsp;settle.</li><li>If&nbsp;a&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;is&nbsp;resolved&nbsp;with&nbsp;another&nbsp;Promise,&nbsp;it&nbsp;will&nbsp;adopt&nbsp;the&nbsp;state&nbsp;of&nbsp;that&nbsp;inner&nbsp;Promise,&nbsp;effectively&nbsp;“flattening”&nbsp;the&nbsp;result.</li></ul><p></p><p>Wrong&nbsp;answers:</p><ul><li>Once&nbsp;a&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;is&nbsp;rejected,&nbsp;<code>.then()</code>&nbsp;handlers&nbsp;will&nbsp;still&nbsp;run&nbsp;automatically&nbsp;unless&nbsp;you&nbsp;explicitly&nbsp;call&nbsp;<code>.catch()</code>.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;rejected&nbsp;promises&nbsp;skip&nbsp;<code>.then()</code>&nbsp;success&nbsp;handlers.</li></ul></li><li>A&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;can&nbsp;resolve&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;times&nbsp;as&nbsp;long&nbsp;as&nbsp;the&nbsp;previous&nbsp;resolution&nbsp;was&nbsp;a&nbsp;primitive&nbsp;value,&nbsp;not&nbsp;an&nbsp;object.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;can&nbsp;settle&nbsp;only&nbsp;once.</li></ul></li><li><code>.finally()</code>&nbsp;receives&nbsp;the&nbsp;resolved&nbsp;value&nbsp;or&nbsp;error&nbsp;as&nbsp;an&nbsp;argument&nbsp;so&nbsp;you&nbsp;can&nbsp;handle&nbsp;results&nbsp;without&nbsp;repeating&nbsp;logic.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;<code>finally</code>&nbsp;receives&nbsp;no&nbsp;arguments.</li></ul></li><li>A&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;executor&nbsp;function&nbsp;begins&nbsp;only&nbsp;after&nbsp;the&nbsp;first&nbsp;<code>.then()</code>&nbsp;is&nbsp;attached,&nbsp;allowing&nbsp;lazy&nbsp;evaluation.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;executor&nbsp;runs&nbsp;immediately.</li></ul></li><li>A&nbsp;Promise&nbsp;automatically&nbsp;catches&nbsp;any&nbsp;exceptions&nbsp;thrown&nbsp;in&nbsp;asynchronous&nbsp;callbacks&nbsp;(like&nbsp;setTimeout),&nbsp;converting&nbsp;them&nbsp;into&nbsp;a&nbsp;rejected&nbsp;Promise.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;exceptions&nbsp;thrown&nbsp;in&nbsp;external&nbsp;async&nbsp;callbacks&nbsp;do&nbsp;not&nbsp;get&nbsp;captured&nbsp;by&nbsp;the&nbsp;original&nbsp;Promise.</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, '{}', true, '2025-12-03 09:00:20.887583+00', '2025-12-03 12:11:44.881715+00');
INSERT INTO public.questions (id, question_type, difficulty, topic, question, answer, quiz, match_keywords, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (49, 'multiple_choice', 'hard', 'Architectural pattern', '<p>What&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;Hexagonal&nbsp;Architecture?</p>', '<p>Hexagonal&nbsp;Architecture&nbsp;separates&nbsp;the&nbsp;application&nbsp;core&nbsp;from&nbsp;external&nbsp;systems&nbsp;using&nbsp;ports&nbsp;and&nbsp;adapters.&nbsp;The&nbsp;core&nbsp;defines&nbsp;ports&nbsp;(interfaces),&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;outside&nbsp;world&nbsp;provides&nbsp;adapters&nbsp;that&nbsp;implement&nbsp;them,&nbsp;such&nbsp;as&nbsp;databases,&nbsp;APIs,&nbsp;or&nbsp;UIs.&nbsp;This&nbsp;keeps&nbsp;the&nbsp;business&nbsp;logic&nbsp;independent&nbsp;from&nbsp;frameworks&nbsp;and&nbsp;technology&nbsp;choices.&nbsp;Dependencies&nbsp;always&nbsp;point&nbsp;inward,&nbsp;making&nbsp;the&nbsp;core&nbsp;easy&nbsp;to&nbsp;test&nbsp;and&nbsp;replace&nbsp;adapters&nbsp;without&nbsp;changing&nbsp;the&nbsp;core.&nbsp;The&nbsp;result&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;flexible,&nbsp;maintainable,&nbsp;framework-agnostic&nbsp;application&nbsp;structure.</p><p></p><p><strong>Correct&nbsp;answers</strong>:</p><ul><li>It&nbsp;separates&nbsp;the&nbsp;application&nbsp;core&nbsp;from&nbsp;external&nbsp;systems&nbsp;by&nbsp;communicating&nbsp;through&nbsp;ports&nbsp;and&nbsp;adapters.</li><li>The&nbsp;core&nbsp;defines&nbsp;ports&nbsp;as&nbsp;interfaces,&nbsp;and&nbsp;external&nbsp;systems&nbsp;such&nbsp;as&nbsp;databases,&nbsp;APIs,&nbsp;or&nbsp;UIs&nbsp;provide&nbsp;adapters&nbsp;that&nbsp;implement&nbsp;those&nbsp;ports.</li><li>It&nbsp;keeps&nbsp;business&nbsp;logic&nbsp;independent&nbsp;from&nbsp;frameworks,&nbsp;infrastructure,&nbsp;and&nbsp;technology-specific&nbsp;details.</li><li>All&nbsp;dependencies&nbsp;point&nbsp;inward&nbsp;toward&nbsp;the&nbsp;core,&nbsp;making&nbsp;the&nbsp;central&nbsp;logic&nbsp;easy&nbsp;to&nbsp;test&nbsp;and&nbsp;unaffected&nbsp;by&nbsp;changes&nbsp;to&nbsp;external&nbsp;systems.</li><li>The&nbsp;architecture&nbsp;is&nbsp;flexible&nbsp;and&nbsp;maintainable&nbsp;because&nbsp;adapters&nbsp;can&nbsp;be&nbsp;swapped&nbsp;without&nbsp;modifying&nbsp;the&nbsp;core&nbsp;application&nbsp;logic.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Wrong&nbsp;answers</strong>:</p><ul><li>Hexagonal&nbsp;Architecture&nbsp;requires&nbsp;each&nbsp;external&nbsp;system&nbsp;to&nbsp;depend&nbsp;directly&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;database&nbsp;layer&nbsp;for&nbsp;persistence.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;external&nbsp;systems&nbsp;interact&nbsp;through&nbsp;adapters,&nbsp;not&nbsp;directly&nbsp;through&nbsp;a&nbsp;database&nbsp;layer.</li></ul></li><li>The&nbsp;core&nbsp;depends&nbsp;on&nbsp;adapter&nbsp;implementations&nbsp;so&nbsp;it&nbsp;can&nbsp;control&nbsp;how&nbsp;databases&nbsp;or&nbsp;UIs&nbsp;behave.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;the&nbsp;core&nbsp;never&nbsp;depends&nbsp;on&nbsp;adapters.</li></ul></li><li>Hexagonal&nbsp;Architecture&nbsp;mandates&nbsp;the&nbsp;use&nbsp;of&nbsp;a&nbsp;specific&nbsp;framework&nbsp;that&nbsp;provides&nbsp;built-in&nbsp;port&nbsp;and&nbsp;adapter&nbsp;abstractions.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;explicitly&nbsp;framework-agnostic.</li></ul></li><li>Ports&nbsp;are&nbsp;concrete&nbsp;classes&nbsp;that&nbsp;directly&nbsp;connect&nbsp;the&nbsp;core&nbsp;to&nbsp;external&nbsp;systems&nbsp;without&nbsp;abstractions.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;ports&nbsp;are&nbsp;abstract&nbsp;interfaces,&nbsp;not&nbsp;concrete&nbsp;classes.</li></ul></li><li>Hexagonal&nbsp;Architecture&nbsp;requires&nbsp;using&nbsp;six&nbsp;layers&nbsp;arranged&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;literal&nbsp;hexagon&nbsp;to&nbsp;structure&nbsp;the&nbsp;project.<ul><li>Incorrect:&nbsp;“hexagon”&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;metaphor;&nbsp;the&nbsp;shape&nbsp;has&nbsp;no&nbsp;technical&nbsp;meaning.</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, '{}', true, '2025-12-03 19:33:52.362272+00', '2025-12-03 19:38:11.792376+00');
